[1
Date: Thu 14 Dec 2000 10:32:15 -0500
From: Chuck Fenwick <chuckf@medicalcorps.org>

I have been following BSE and the growth of BSE-"like" problems for some
time. The chronic wasting disease in elk brings to mind several questions:
1) Were the elk farms using animal-based feed?
2) When the domestic herds were replenished from the wild were they fed the
same feed OR is the contamination caused from:
a. contact with infected animals? or
b. contact with the soil or water?
Chuck Fenwick, Director
Medical Corps
<chuckf@medicalcorps.org>
******
[2
Date: Thu, 14 Dec 2000 07:31:37 -0800
From: Kathryn M.Tominey <kathryn.tominey@pnl.gov>

Have the involved ministries also put out alerts to hunters and others
about absolutely avoiding meat from sick or suspect animals since the
disease is so closely related to BSE and scrapie?
Kathryn M. Tominey
Systems & Risk Analysis
Pacific Northwest National Laboratory
<kathryn.tominey@pnl.gov>
